Veteran Harambee Stars, AFC Leopards fan Isaac Juma has died following an attack by an assailant at his home in Mumias, Kakamega County. Police said they have arrested a suspect over the attack. The officers handling the matter said preliminary findings had shown the attack was out of a land dispute in the area. Officials said Juma was slashed to death by the assailant on Wednesday at around 11 pm. Juma was a passionate football lover and religiously supported the national team, Harambee Stars. Western Regional police boss Peris Muthoni said they are interrogating the suspect for more information. “We have a suspect over the murder to know more,” she said. Juma was a passionate football lover and religiously supported the national team, Harambee Stars. He also supported AFC Leopards. His wife told police the incident happened over a land dispute that has been outstanding. The body was later picked up and taken to the local mortuary as investigations go on.